Evertop Realties Limited has unveiled two Nigerian actors as its brand ambassadors. According to a statement by the firm, the ambassadors are Jeff Owolewa popularly known as Tony Montana and Olayinka Solomon popularly known as ‘Ogo Mushin’. “The new ambassadors will join forces with Abidemi Kosoko who has been the face of the brand in recent years,” the firm said. Speaking at the unveiling, the Managing Director, Evertop Realties Limited, Mr Oluwaseun Joseph, said the choice of both thespians was based on their distinct reputation and character which aligned with the company’s values. He said, “We are a trusted brand in this market and our choice of ambassadors matches what we stand for. We are sure that the amiable character of these Nollywood stars will continue to enhance our brand equity and patronage. “We are pleased to have them onboard and they will help complement the effort of Abidemi Kosoko who has been a good ambassador of the Evertop brand for years.” Commenting on the partnership, Owolewa said, “Evertop is an household name in the Nigerian real estate market. They have built a name on selling choice properties across Nigeria for years. “Being the face of this brand means I can vouch for them. And I assure anyone willing to buy land, house or seeking property advisory to contact Evertop Realties Limited. You won’t regret it.” Solomon also said buying properties from Evertop is safe and genuine. He said, “Buying properties from Evertop guarantees you peace of mind. They are a certified company. So anyone who buys properties from them won’t face speculator challenges or have any issue with certificate of ownership with the government.”  Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com